# ============================================================
# DETAIL CORE IMPLEMENTATION
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: implementation
domain: detail
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

purpose:
Defines core implementation responsibilities for detail.

scope:
Covers validators, resolvers, filters,
selectors, revision linkers, history readers,
trace emitters, and failure-code emitters.

design_intent:
Implementation must realize detail behavior explicitly.
The core implementation model exists to prevent detail logic
from being scattered into UI glue or unmanaged runtime branches.

implementation_components:
- detail validator
- detail resolver
- visibility filter
- lifecycle selector
- revision linker
- history retriever
- trace emitter
- failure mapper

handler_contracts:
- validate(detail_input) -> validation_result
- resolve(target_ref, detail_type, mode) -> detail_candidates
- select_active(detail_candidates) -> primary_detail
- filter_visibility(primary_detail, actor_scope) -> allowed_or_masked_detail
- link_revision(current_detail, prior_detail) -> revision_chain_result
- read_history(target_ref, detail_type, history_mode) -> historical_detail_set
- emit_trace(event_type, context) -> trace_result

required_behavior:
- Reject invalid detail before exposure.
- Select active detail deterministically.
- Preserve revision chain.
- Support historical mode and audit mode.
- Emit stable failure codes.

failure_codes:
- DETAIL_IMPL_VALIDATION_FAILED
- DETAIL_IMPL_RESOLUTION_FAILED
- DETAIL_IMPL_SELECTION_FAILED
- DETAIL_IMPL_VISIBILITY_FILTER_FAILED
- DETAIL_IMPL_REVISION_LINK_FAILED
- DETAIL_IMPL_HISTORY_READ_FAILED
- DETAIL_IMPL_TRACE_EMIT_FAILED

example_scenarios:
- A valid detail input is validated, resolved, selected, filtered, and traced.
- A revision request fails because prior linkage is missing.
- A historical read succeeds without touching current-active selection.
